.hero
  .container
    = image_tag "logo.svg", data: {svg_fallback: "/assets/images/logo.png"}
    %h1 The Berlin Rationalist Community
    %p Heute besser als gestern; morgen besser als heute.

.container
  %section#start.section-kits
    .section-title
      %h3 Our efforts in Berlin consist of

    %ul.kits
      %li
        = link_to "http://github.com/thoughtbot/proteus-middleman" do
          = image_tag "middleman.svg", data: {svg_fallback: "/assets/images/middleman.png"}
          %h3 A Meetup
        %p Semi-regular schelling point for everyone interested
      %li
        = link_to "http://github.com/thoughtbot/proteus-jekyll" do
          = image_tag "jekyll.svg", data: {svg_fallback: "/assets/images/jekyll.png"}
          %h3 A Dojo
        %p A weekly meeting focussed on applyinf and practicing rationality techniques
      %li
        = link_to "http://github.com/thoughtbot/proteus-gulp" do
          = image_tag "gulp.svg", data: {svg_fallback: "/assets/images/gulp.png"}
          %h3 A Mailing List
        %p For coordination and discussion

    = link_to "View the kits on Github", "https://github.com/thoughtbot/proteus", class: "button"

  %section
    .section-title
      %h3 What's included?
    %p.intro Proteus is a collection of useful starter kits to help you launch your static site or prototype faster. They follow the #{link_to "thoughtbot styleguide", "https://github.com/thoughtbot/guides/tree/master/style"} and include our favorite front end tools:

    %ul.tools
      %li.tool-haml
        = link_to "http://haml.info" do
          .icon
            = image_tag "haml.svg", data: {svg_fallback: "/assets/images/haml.png"}
          .info
            %h3 HAML
            %p Simple template markup
      %li.tool-coffeescript
        = link_to "http://coffeescript.org" do
          .icon
            = image_tag "coffeescript.svg", data: {svg_fallback: "/assets/images/coffeescript.png"}
          .info
            %h3 Coffeescript
            %p Beats writing javascript
      %li.tool-sass
        = link_to "http://sass-lang.com" do
          .icon
            = image_tag "sass.svg", data: {svg_fallback: "/assets/images/sass.png"}
          .info
            %h3 Sass
            %p CSS with superpowers
      %li.tool-bourbon
        = link_to "http://bourbon.io" do
          .icon
            = image_tag "bourbon.svg", data: {svg_fallback: "/assets/images/bourbon.png"}
          .info
            %h3 Bourbon
            %p Sass mixin library
      %li.tool-neat
        = link_to "http://neat.bourbon.io" do
          .icon
            = image_tag "neat.svg", data: {svg_fallback: "/assets/images/neat.png"}
          .info
            %h3 Neat
            %p Semantic grid
      %li.tool-bitters
        = link_to "http://bitters.bourbon.io" do
          .icon
            = image_tag "bitters.svg", data: {svg_fallback: "/assets/images/bitters.png"}
          .info
            %h3 Bitters
            %p Styles, variables and structure

  %section.section-gem
    .section-title
      = image_tag "gem.svg", data: {svg_fallback: "/assets/images/gem.png"}
      %h3 A gem to make it even easier

    %p Just run this to install it:

    %pre
      %code gem install proteus-kits

    %p Then pick the project you want to start (i.e. Middleman)

    %pre
      %code proteus new middleman your-project-name

    %p We've also included some handy shortcuts for you to use in your kit:
    %ul
      %li
        %code proteus setup
        \: Installs dependencies
      %li
        %code proteus server
        \: Runs the server
      %li
        %code proteus deploy
        \: Deploys your site to Github Pages

  %section.section-faq
    .section-title
      %h3 Questions
    %dl
      %dt What's up with the name?
      %dd Proteus was an early Greek sea god and a shapeshifter. The English word "protean" means "able to do many things, change easily, versatile". We use static site generators to <em>prot</em>otype apps and sites quickly, so it seemed like a good fit.

      %dt I found a bug / Have an improvement / Want to help
      %dd
        Great! The best way to make the kits better is to open an Issue on that kit on Github. Bonus points if you submit a Pull Request to fix a problem. Ask <a href="http://twitter.com/joshuaogle">@joshuaogle</a> if you have any questions on where to get started.

      %dt My favorite generator isn't listed!
      %dd
        We'll be adding more as we find ourselves using more of them. Can't wait? Put together a template that includes the tools listed above and
        = link_to "open a pull request", "https://github.com/thoughtbot/proteus/pulls"
        adding it to the list.
